29:10.633 --> 29:11.633
Now, Jonathan,

29:11.800 --> 29:14.467
I'm going to give you some
very explicit instructions.

29:14.533 --> 29:17.900
I need you to do exactly
what I tell you to do.

29:17.967 --> 29:19.933
-Can you do that, Jonathan?
-I will try my best.

29:20.400 --> 29:21.700
Excellent. I know you can do it.

29:21.767 --> 29:22.800
-You're married, right?
-Yes.

29:22.867 --> 29:24.533
-You know how to follow instructions well.
-Yes.

29:24.600 --> 29:25.867
All right.

29:26.200 --> 29:28.367
Here's what we'll do.
We'll divide the cards

29:28.433 --> 29:29.867
so they're half-and-half-ish.

29:29.933 --> 29:31.767
You're gonna take one half.
I'm gonna take one half.

29:31.833 --> 29:33.000
Which half would you like?

29:33.067 --> 29:34.300
This half.

29:34.367 --> 29:35.367
That half. Go for it.

29:35.433 --> 29:37.033
Give that half a shuffle, if you would.

29:37.100 --> 29:38.633
Really mix it up well there.

29:40.200 --> 29:42.133
-More shuffle?
-However much you'd like.

29:42.200 --> 29:43.800
-It's up to you.
-They're fully shuffled.

29:43.967 --> 29:45.533
Great. Now, I'm going to turn around

29:45.600 --> 29:48.067
so that I can't possibly see what
you're doing, Jonathan,

29:48.167 --> 29:49.467
but what I would like you to do

29:49.633 --> 29:51.033
is please spread the cards out,

29:51.100 --> 29:52.133
you can see, just like this.

29:52.200 --> 29:54.867
Spread the cards out so that
you can see all of the options.

29:54.967 --> 29:55.967
Yep.

29:56.167 --> 29:59.500
And then I'd like you to think
of any one of those cards that you see.

29:59.567 --> 30:01.067
-Okay.
-Have you got one in mind?

30:01.133 --> 30:02.933
I've got most in my mind right now,

30:03.000 --> 30:04.767
but I'll go back to just one.

30:04.833 --> 30:06.700
Okay, I've changed it.
I've got one in my mind.

30:06.767 --> 30:08.933
KRAMER: You've got one in your mind
and you'll remember that card?

30:09.000 --> 30:10.067
I'm gonna try my best.

30:10.133 --> 30:11.800
Terrific. All right, Jonathan.

30:11.867 --> 30:13.267
I'll grab back the cards.

30:13.333 --> 30:15.400
We'll shuffle them all together, in fact.

30:15.800 --> 30:17.900
And are you ready
for your next instructions?

30:17.967 --> 30:19.200
-Yes.
-You've been doing very well

30:19.267 --> 30:20.833
-following instructions so far.
-Thank you.

30:21.167 --> 30:22.733
Make sure they're nice and mixed up.

30:22.800 --> 30:24.900
Would you hold out...
You're right-handed, yes?

30:25.067 --> 30:26.767
Would you hold out
your left hand actually,

30:26.833 --> 30:28.700
because I'm going to have
you deal some cards.

30:28.767 --> 30:29.800
ROSS: Okay.

30:29.900 --> 30:32.333
All right, terrific.
This is so that the cards are entirely

30:32.400 --> 30:33.900
out of my control right now.

30:33.967 --> 30:35.033
Jonathan,
you've got the cards right there.

30:35.100 --> 30:36.133
I have the power.

30:36.200 --> 30:38.000
Now, what I'm going to ask you to do

30:38.067 --> 30:40.733
is please deal the cards facedown

30:41.300 --> 30:42.567
-onto my palm...
-Okay.

30:42.633 --> 30:46.133
Starting from the top of the deck,
until I say stop.

30:46.200 --> 30:48.967
All right, and by the way, now that the
cards are completely out of my control,

30:49.033 --> 30:51.200
you can let everyone know,
what's the card you're just thinking of.

30:51.367 --> 30:53.967
I thought of the eight of diamonds.

30:54.300 --> 30:55.900
-The eight of diamonds.
-Yes.

30:56.133 --> 30:57.133
All right, well,

30:57.200 --> 30:59.967
please go ahead and I'd like
you to start dealing down cards there

31:00.100 --> 31:01.167
until I say stop.

31:03.133 --> 31:04.200
Oh, stop.

31:05.433 --> 31:07.433
It was quick,
but it was good while it lasted.

31:08.100 --> 31:09.367
(LAUGHING)

31:10.667 --> 31:11.733
I've...

31:11.967 --> 31:14.067
I've heard that far too often in my life.

31:14.467 --> 31:15.600
(LAUGHING)

31:15.800 --> 31:17.867
Now, Jonathan, just to recap
here for a moment.

31:17.933 --> 31:19.267
You looked at the cards,

31:19.333 --> 31:21.900
you were thinking in your mind
of a single card.

31:21.967 --> 31:23.267
You shuffled the deck.

31:23.333 --> 31:24.967
You dealt the cards.

31:25.167 --> 31:26.200
Absolutely.

31:26.333 --> 31:28.667
Right here, the card you're
thinking of, Jonathan.

31:29.333 --> 31:30.467
The eight of diamonds.

31:30.533 --> 31:32.500
Eight of diamonds. Let's see how we did.
Go for it.

31:32.633 --> 31:34.900
Wow! Holy moly.

31:34.967 --> 31:36.333
(CHEERS AND APPLAUSE)

31:36.800 --> 31:38.267
Thank you very much.

31:38.367 --> 31:40.600
-Thank you, Jonathan.
-That was fabulous.

31:40.700 --> 31:42.000
No idea how that...

31:42.500 --> 31:43.967
'Cause I had hold of them
all the time there.

31:44.133 --> 31:45.500
So Penn and Teller are gonna talk

31:45.567 --> 31:47.100
and work out if they can work out
how you did that.

31:47.167 --> 31:48.200
I was kind of on top of it there.

31:48.267 --> 31:50.167
I couldn't see anything. I had no idea.

31:50.233 --> 31:51.600
Let me ask you about
you're schooling, though.

31:51.667 --> 31:53.533
-Sure.
-You speak four languages, is that right?

31:53.700 --> 31:55.367
-I do.
-What are those languages?

31:55.500 --> 31:59.233
I speak English, French, Spanish,
and Swahili.

31:59.300 --> 32:01.800
Wow. Well, I can see why you'd want
to learn some of them,

32:01.867 --> 32:03.933
-but why French?
-(LAUGHING)

32:04.767 --> 32:06.400
-I know. Nobody speaks that language.
-That's crazy.

32:08.233 --> 32:11.133
What's the situation for you
being a woman in magic?

32:11.467 --> 32:14.367
What are the advantages,
and what are the disadvantages of that?

32:14.567 --> 32:17.000
You know, I think there are
advantages and disadvantages.

32:17.067 --> 32:20.833
You know, advantages being that,
I guess, you sort of stand out

32:20.900 --> 32:22.433
just by nature of being a woman.

32:22.567 --> 32:24.367
Disadvantages also being

32:24.433 --> 32:26.700
that things can be a little bit more
challenging.

32:26.767 --> 32:29.800
You know, the magic books are written
for men

32:29.867 --> 32:31.767
and men's clothing and that type of thing.

32:31.833 --> 32:33.233
Yes, because if you're wearing
a big jacket,

32:33.300 --> 32:36.333
then you could conceal stuff more easily
than coming out with bare sleeves.

32:36.400 --> 32:37.900
Exactly, exactly.

32:37.967 --> 32:39.433
Okay, well, I think they're ready now.

32:39.500 --> 32:40.800
They've deliberated long enough.

32:40.900 --> 32:43.367
-Penn?
-Well, you know, the temptation,

32:43.933 --> 32:46.633
because women in magic are so rare

32:47.067 --> 32:50.600
is to talk about how refreshing it is
to see someone with a couple of

32:50.933 --> 32:52.300
X chromosomes up there,

32:52.733 --> 32:56.267
but I don't think that's
the most interesting thing about this.

32:56.800 --> 32:59.333
The most interesting thing about
this is not your gender

32:59.567 --> 33:01.367
but rather that...

33:01.533 --> 33:05.700
What you did is a trick, and the audience
probably can't tell the difference.

33:05.767 --> 33:07.067
What you did is a trick

33:07.133 --> 33:09.233
was predominately intellectual.

33:09.967 --> 33:12.767
And a lot of the people that
come out here and do tricks

33:12.833 --> 33:14.167
it's finger flinging,

33:14.233 --> 33:16.100
it's what I would call juggling.

33:16.467 --> 33:20.333
It's a huge amount of physical practice.

33:20.400 --> 33:22.033
What you were doing there

33:22.167 --> 33:24.300
is a huge amount of mental practice.

33:24.667 --> 33:27.200
As a matter of fact, when you got
to the place when you had to do

33:27.300 --> 33:30.967
a shuffle that...
Well, you had to do your shuffle...

33:31.100 --> 33:32.500
-Yes.
-You could see

33:32.567 --> 33:34.700
that your handling of the cards

33:34.833 --> 33:37.233
was not as smooth as
your handling of your mind.

33:37.500 --> 33:40.100
I'm gonna say a couple of names to you.

33:40.167 --> 33:41.700
There's a great Spanish magician

33:41.833 --> 33:43.767
named Juan Tamariz

33:43.833 --> 33:47.200
and there's another great Chicago magician
named Aronson.

33:48.200 --> 33:49.733
And I bet that either of those two guys

33:49.967 --> 33:52.733
have a pretty good idea
of the capacity you have.

33:52.800 --> 33:57.667
Now, I wanna tell you, my favorite kinds
of card tricks use this technique,

33:57.733 --> 33:59.767
'cause I love it when it's up here
instead of here.

34:00.367 --> 34:02.033
-Okay.
-We got a pretty good idea?

34:02.233 --> 34:04.233
-Absolutely.
-Okay.

34:04.367 --> 34:06.133
I'm assuming that that kind of...

34:06.200 --> 34:07.800
The codes and the names mentioned there,
that's enough

34:07.867 --> 34:10.233
for you to believe that they
know what you were doing?

34:10.300 --> 34:11.533
-It is.
-It was all done up here,

34:11.600 --> 34:12.667
Jonathan, all done up here.

34:13.333 --> 34:14.367
That's why I was so good to work with,

34:14.433 --> 34:15.800
-'cause nothing was being done up here.
-(LAUGHING)

34:16.400 --> 34:17.632
ROSS: But you were fantastic.

34:17.699 --> 34:19.800
It blew us all away for sure,
even if you didn't fool them.

34:19.867 --> 34:21.167
Jen was wonderful, wasn't she?

34:21.233 --> 34:23.000
-Jen Kramer, ladies and gentlemen.
-(CHEERS AND APPLAUSE)

34:23.067 --> 34:24.500
That was fabulous.

34:24.567 --> 34:25.900
Jen Kramer.

34:26.233 --> 34:27.500
Thank you very much.

34:30.233 --> 34:33.132
Out of all of our acts tonight,
I feel confident in saying,

34:33.199 --> 34:37.300
our final one is without a doubt our most
famous and definitely our best looking.

34:37.433 --> 34:41.067
It's also their show, so they may or
may not have made me say that last part.

34:41.132 --> 34:42.367
Okay, it's time to see them do a trick.

34:42.433 --> 34:45.033
Ladies and gentlemen,
go crazy for Penn and Teller.

34:45.100 --> 34:47.333
(CHEERS AND APPLAUSE)

34:51.467 --> 34:52.667
We'd like to...

34:52.933 --> 34:55.500
We'd like to address a classic of magic,

34:55.567 --> 34:56.900
or actually the classic of magic.

34:56.967 --> 34:59.600
As a matter of fact,
it's the clich√© of magic.

34:59.667 --> 35:02.167
It's a clich√© that when someone
does something impossible

35:02.233 --> 35:04.300
they've pulled a rabbit out of their hat.

35:04.367 --> 35:07.667
And it is the icon of magic

35:07.733 --> 35:11.867
to have a 19th-century magician
with a top hat and a wand, a little tap,

35:11.933 --> 35:13.633
and a live rabbit coming out.

35:13.700 --> 35:15.033
And every magician does this.

35:15.100 --> 35:18.500
Every magician we've had
out here, as part of their routine,

35:18.567 --> 35:20.100
they will pull a rabbit out of their hat.

35:20.167 --> 35:23.233
Every birthday party magician you see,
every backyard magician,

35:23.300 --> 35:25.867
every magician on Broadway,
or on the strip... No.

35:26.233 --> 35:27.233
No.

35:27.300 --> 35:28.967
It's a really rare trick.

35:29.033 --> 35:31.333
It's the clich√© of magic, and yet,

35:31.533 --> 35:34.800
I may see more magic than you,
and I've never seen it,

35:34.933 --> 35:35.967
never once seen it.

35:36.033 --> 35:37.800
Teller sees more magic than I do,

35:37.967 --> 35:40.267
he's never seen it either.
We've never seen that simple trick

35:40.500 --> 35:42.100
of a top hat,

35:42.167 --> 35:46.600
a wand, a couple of taps, and out of there
comes a live rabbit.

35:46.667 --> 35:48.400
There's a few reasons you haven't seen it.

35:48.533 --> 35:51.367
One is it's become an anachronism.

35:51.633 --> 35:54.300
In the 19th century
when this became a clich√©,

35:54.600 --> 35:58.700
many men wore top hats to the theater.
They're called opera hats.

35:58.767 --> 36:00.400
They fold up to go under the seat,

36:00.467 --> 36:03.567
but now, it's very, very rare
to see a man or a woman

36:03.900 --> 36:07.533
wearing a top hat
in 21st-century Las Vegas.

36:07.600 --> 36:09.433
Maybe when there's cosplay in town

36:09.500 --> 36:12.400
or maybe there's somebody
who's into steam punk,

36:12.467 --> 36:13.667
we'll see one or two.

36:13.733 --> 36:15.900
Mostly we see a cowboy hat now and again

36:15.967 --> 36:18.733
and a baseball hat or a cap.

36:18.800 --> 36:21.867
I'm just gonna...
I'm just gonna loan this to you, if I may.

36:21.933 --> 36:24.133
And just, you know, make sure
you fold it up, open it up,

36:24.200 --> 36:25.267
fold it up, open it up,

36:25.333 --> 36:27.867
put it on your head,
kinda make it your own for a little while.

36:27.933 --> 36:29.800
I'm loaning it to you right here.

36:29.867 --> 36:33.133
So since they can't borrow a top hat,

36:33.200 --> 36:36.600
they'll use something else.
They'll use what magicians call a silk,

36:36.667 --> 36:38.700
which is really just a handkerchief.

36:38.767 --> 36:40.467
They could do a lot of routines
with those.

36:40.533 --> 36:42.500
There's a lot of magic developed for this.

36:42.567 --> 36:45.633
And they'll have a picture of a top hat
on a silk

36:45.700 --> 36:48.233
and they'll pull out a rabbit.

36:48.367 --> 36:52.033
But it's a rabbit pulled out
of a picture of a top hat,

36:52.100 --> 36:55.400
not a top hat,
and it's also not a real rabbit.

36:56.100 --> 36:57.633
This is what's called a kicker.

36:57.733 --> 37:00.500
It's sold in magic stores, very expensive.

37:00.667 --> 37:03.200
It's a spring covered in fur,

37:03.267 --> 37:05.933
and if you puppeteer it properly,
which Teller does,

37:06.000 --> 37:08.900
at least in a long shot,
kinda looks like a...

37:09.067 --> 37:11.533
Like a real rabbit.
Makes the magic much easier,

37:11.667 --> 37:13.033
'cause you can compress this.

37:13.167 --> 37:15.400
You can kind of palm it.
You can also hide it up your sleeve.

37:15.633 --> 37:16.667
It's easier to handle this,

37:16.733 --> 37:20.067
and it also deals with another problem,
another anachronism,

37:20.333 --> 37:22.233
which is in the 19th century

37:22.467 --> 37:25.467
we didn't really care very much
how animals were treated.

37:25.533 --> 37:29.300
But the sphere of compassion
for humanity has grown,

37:29.367 --> 37:31.900
and in the 21st century we insist,

37:32.067 --> 37:33.667
magicians and audiences alike,

37:33.933 --> 37:37.067
that a life is treated with compassion,

37:37.233 --> 37:38.500
dignity and respect.

37:38.633 --> 37:43.533
So it makes it really hard
to do the rabbit-out-of-the-hat trick.

37:45.433 --> 37:46.433
(LAUGHING)

37:47.167 --> 37:48.700
Does anybody here have a top hat?

37:48.767 --> 37:50.267
Anybody have a top hat in the audience?

