38:18.700 --> 38:19.833
So I take a magic wand.

38:19.900 --> 38:22.633
Here's the trick that
you wanted to see, the <i>clich√©.</i>

38:22.700 --> 38:24.733
Borrowed top hat, borrowed from Kat.

38:24.833 --> 38:26.300
Couple of taps right here.

38:26.400 --> 38:28.200
Circular gesture,

38:28.267 --> 38:31.400
and then out of that top hat
comes a live...

38:31.467 --> 38:32.700
-You can touch her.
-Really?

38:32.767 --> 38:34.400
He's so cute.

38:34.467 --> 38:37.567
That's Wossy the Rabbit right there,
Wossy.

38:37.633 --> 38:38.867
-Say hi to Wossy.
-Hi, Wossy. Hi!

38:38.933 --> 38:40.433
Is that a real rabbit right there?

38:40.500 --> 38:42.867
-Hi, it is, oh, my God.
-There it is the classic of magic,

38:42.933 --> 38:44.900
a live rabbit out of a borrowed top hat.

38:44.967 --> 38:46.367
-Thank you so much, Kat.
-It's so cute and fluffy.

38:46.433 --> 38:48.600
Right there, watch your step.
Right back there.

38:48.667 --> 38:50.800
That is our rabbit Wossy.

38:50.900 --> 38:52.600
(CHEERS AND APPLAUSE)

38:52.667 --> 38:55.300
Wasn't that great, ladies and gentlemen?
Penn and Teller.

38:55.533 --> 38:58.933
-(CHEERS AND APPLAUSE)
